<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h1 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-interior-angles-of-a-polygon">Inte=
rior angles of a polygon</h1>



<p id=3D"introduction"></p>



<p>Here you will learn about interior angles of a polygon, including how to=
 calculate the sum of interior angles for a polygon, single interior angles=
, and how to use this knowledge to solve problems.</p>



<p></p>



<p>Students will first learn about interior angles of a polygon as part of =
geometry in high school.</p>



<p></p>
</div>
</div>



<p id=3D"what-is"></p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-=
layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-are-interior-angles-of-a-poly=
gon">What are interior angles of a polygon?</h2>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Interior angles of a polygon</strong> are the angles inside a sh=
ape. They are the angles formed between two sides of a polygon.</p>



<p></p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img fetchpriority=3D"hi=
gh" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"431" height=3D"432" src=3D"https://thirdspa=
celearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Interior-angles-of-a-polygon-1-US=
.png" alt=3D"Interior angles of a polygon 1 US" class=3D"wp-image-251751" s=
tyle=3D"width:220px"></figure>
</div>


<p></p>



<p>The interior and exterior angles of a polygon form a straight line and a=
re therefore supplementary =E2=80=93 together, they add up to <span class=
=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"ka=
tex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Mat=
h/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>180</mn><mo lspace=3D"0em" rspace=3D"0=
em">=E2=88=98</mo></msup><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">.</mi></mrow><annotatio=
n encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 180^{\circ}. </annotation></semantics></m=
ath></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"b=
ase"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6741em;"></span><span class=
=3D"mord">18</span><span class=3D"mord"><span class=3D"mord">0</span><span =
class=3D"msupsub"><span class=3D"vlist-t"><span class=3D"vlist-r"><span cla=
ss=3D"vlist" style=3D"height: 0.6741em;"><span class=3D"" style=3D"top: -3.=
063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class=3D"pstrut" style=3D"height: 2.7em=
;"></span><span class=3D"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class=3D"mo=
rd mtight"><span class=3D"mord mtight">=E2=88=98</span></span></span></span=
></span></span></span></span></span><span class=3D"mord">.</span></span></s=
pan></span></span></p>



<p></p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img decoding=3D"async" =
width=3D"531" height=3D"399" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-conte=
nt/uploads/2024/08/Interior-angles-of-a-polygon-2-US.png" alt=3D"Interior a=
ngles of a polygon 2 US" class=3D"wp-image-251752" style=3D"width:320px"></=
figure>
</div>


<p></p>



<p>You can calculate the sum of the interior angles of a polygon by splitti=
ng it into triangles and multiplying the number of triangles by <span class=
=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"ka=
tex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Mat=
h/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>180</mn><mo lspace=3D"0em" rspace=3D"0=
em">=E2=88=98</mo></msup><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">.</mi></mrow><annotatio=
n encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 180^{\circ}. </annotation></semantics></m=
ath></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"b=
ase"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6741em;"></span><span class=
=3D"mord">18</span><span class=3D"mord"><span class=3D"mord">0</span><span =
class=3D"msupsub"><span class=3D"vlist-t"><span class=3D"vlist-r"><span cla=
ss=3D"vlist" style=3D"height: 0.6741em;"><span class=3D"" style=3D"top: -3.=
063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class=3D"pstrut" style=3D"height: 2.7em=
;"></span><span class=3D"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class=3D"mo=
rd mtight"><span class=3D"mord mtight">=E2=88=98</span></span></span></span=
></span></span></span></span></span><span class=3D"mord">.</span></span></s=
pan></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p>The number of triangles a polygon can be split into is always <span clas=
s=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"k=
atex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Ma=
th/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"applic=
ation/x-tex"> 2 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex=
-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" styl=
e=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=3D"mord">2</span></span></span><=
/span></span> less than the number of sides it has.</p>



<p></p>



<p>For example,</p>



<p></p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img decoding=3D"async" =
width=3D"874" height=3D"252" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-conte=
nt/uploads/2024/08/Interior-angles-of-a-polygon-3-US.png" alt=3D"Interior a=
ngles of a polygon 3 US" class=3D"wp-image-251753" style=3D"width:720px"></=
figure>
</div>


<p></p>



<p>A Heptagon has <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-displa=
y=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=
=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><=
annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 7 </annotation></semantics></mat=
h></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"bas=
e"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=3D"=
mord">7</span></span></span></span></span> sides.</p>



<p></p>



<p><span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><sp=
an class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w=
