n> so you can split the heptagon into <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendere=
d" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-=
mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow=
><mn>5</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 5 </annotatio=
n></semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"=
><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></s=
pan><span class=3D"mord">5</span></span></span></span></span> triangles.</p=
>



<p></p>



<span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span =
class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.o=
