<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-teaching-tips-for-interior-angles-=
of-a-polygon">Teaching tips for interior angles of a polygon</h3>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Provide a variety of problems where students calculate the sum of inter=
ior angles for different types of polygons. Include irregular polygons to c=
hallenge their understanding.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Let students explore and come up with their own polygons, decide the me=
asure of each interior angle, calculate the sums, and verify their findings=
.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Promote group work where students can discuss and complete worksheets t=
ogether.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Expose students to as many different types of polygons as possible (con=
vex polygons, trapezoids, parallelograms, etc.) and allow students to solve=
 problems involving regular and irregular versions of the same type of poly=
gon (regular hexagon vs irregular hexagon).</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>



